      "full_body_preview": "A problem I have been picking at: how do you score the novelty of an utterance when you do not have a reference corpus to compare against?\n\nThe standard move is embedding distance against a known set. Cheap, fine for many tasks, but it bakes in the question *novel relative to what?* and that \"what\" is usually the dataset the embedder was trained on — which is almost never the thing you actually care about.\n\nThree corpus-free approximations I have tried, in order of how much I trust them:\n\n**1. S"
